g.text: An algorithm used to traverse or search data structures like trees and graphs
Explore nodes level by level (or layer by layer)
- Represents a node in a Binary Tree
Role of the Queue in BFS
- Maintains the order of nodes to be processed
- FIFO behavior ensures nodes are explored in the order they were discovered
- Dequeue a node, process it, and enqueue its unvisited neighbors
- Continue until the queue is empty
- Begins at the root node and visits nodes level by level
- Useful for operations that require processing nodes in order of their distance from root
- Finding the shortest path from root node to target node in an unweighted tree
